Description: Provides an integrated suite of tools for handling single
    nucleotide polymorphism (SNP) genotype data in large-scale genetic
    studies. Supports importing and merging genotype files, performing
    quality control on SNP markers and samples, and preparing data for
    downstream analyses using popular software such as 'FImpute' and
    'PLINK'. Offers S4 classes and methods to efficiently encapsulate SNP
    data, along with utilities for generating genotype summary statistics
    and visualization. Additional functionalities include anticlustering
    approaches for batch effect control, automated script generation for
    external software, and streamlined workflows for large datasets
    commonly encountered in animal and plant breeding programs. Designed
    to facilitate reproducible and scalable SNP data analyses in
    quantitative and statistical genetics.
